# Runtime secrets for the Worker (dotenv format).
#
# - The "Deploy to Cloudflare" button reads this file and prompts for each
#   value during setup, storing them as encrypted Worker secrets.
# - For local development, copy this file to `.dev.vars` and fill it in.
# - For a manual deploy, set each one with: wrangler secret put <NAME>
#
# `.dev.vars` itself is git-ignored; only this example is committed.

# These two are the ONLY auth secrets — they are deliberately NOT editable from
# the admin dashboard. Everything else (site name, community name + link,
# Turnstile keys, public base URL) can be configured at runtime under
# /admin → Settings, so a fresh deploy only strictly needs the two below.

# Required ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Password for the /admin dashboard sign-in. Choose a strong, unique value;
# repeated wrong guesses are rate-limited and locked out per IP.
ADMIN_PASSWORD=""
# Secret used to sign admin session cookies. Generate with:
#   openssl rand -base64 32
SESSION_SECRET=""

# Optional ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Uncomment and fill in only the features you want to enable. All of these can
# also be set later from the admin dashboard (Settings), which takes precedence.

# Cloudflare Turnstile secret (anti-spam). Pair with the TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY
# var in wrangler.json (or set both from the dashboard).
# TURNSTILE_SECRET=""
